class Solution {
    public int countDigitOne(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        long i = 1;
        while (i <= n) {
            long divider = i * 10;
            count += (n / divider) * i + Math.min(Math.max(n % divider - i + 1, 0), i);
            i *= 10;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterates through each digit position, calculating the number of times '1' appears at that position in all numbers up to n, leveraging mathematical properties to avoid explicit iteration over all numbers.
